text: Anne Grommerch (11 December 1970 - 15 April 2016) was a French politician. She was a member of the National Assembly of France. She was born in Thionville. She represented the Moselle department, and was a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. She replaced Jean-Marie Demange. Grommerch was also elected Mayor of Thionville in 2014. Grommerch developed breast cancer in 2007. She died as a result of the disease on 15 April 2016 at the age of 45. ==References== Category:1970 births Category:2016 deaths Category:Deaths from breast cancer Category:French mayors Category:Politicians from Grand Est Category:People from Moselle
